external_knowledge:
- The occupation with the highest median income and growth rate is likely to be one that is in-demand and has a high percentage of the population; 
- The query assumes that the income categories are mutually exclusive and that each occupation can only belong to one income category; 
- The query also assumes that the median income and growth rate are the most important factors in determining the ranking of occupations.

sql:
SELECT occupation_name, median_income
FROM occupations
ORDER BY median_income DESC;

SELECT occupation_name
FROM occupations
WHERE median_income = (SELECT MAX(median_income) FROM occupations);

SELECT AVG(median_income) AS average_median_income
FROM occupations
WHERE is_in_demand = 1 AND median_income > 50000;

SELECT occupation_name
FROM occupations
WHERE is_in_demand = 1 AND median_income > 50000;
